text: An incredible cast of actors, mainly up and coming, minus veterans Jill Scott, Dan Ackroyd and Craig Robinson. However, Get On Up's main sour point is that there was too much flashing back and forth between scenes and timelines to ever connect or sympathize with any on screen characters. The movie's 1st half hour randomly cuts through different eras in a scrambled motion. Nice effort but its not touching Ray by s long shot!
